    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p>Collections on a/c Occident<lb/> from <persName>I. Cohen</persName> 900<lb/> rep comp
                    <hi rend="underline">180</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">$7.20</hi></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir, I hand you<lb/> enclosed my check on Mechanic<lb/> Bank
                    <placeName>New York</placeName>, for<lb/> Seven 20/ Dolls proceeds 50<lb/>
                collections from <persName>Jacob<lb/> Cohen Esqr.</persName> I remit this small<lb/>
                amount because I think<lb/> every dollar you can re-<lb/>=ceive at present you<lb/>
                can find use for in your<lb/>
                <sic>enterprize</sic>. I regretted much<lb/> in finding you absent from
                        <placeName>Phil<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName> on my sojourn there<lb/> I
                hope your printer &amp; stereo<lb/>-type are progressing rapidly<lb/> to a
                conclusion, as the<lb/> people are very anx</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>=ious to see the Bible—<lb/> What is the meaning<lb/> of <persName>D<hi rend="sup"
                        >r</hi>. Wise</persName> being called<lb/> to the City of
                        <placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic></placeName><lb/> to take charge of what
                was<lb/> hitherto considered an<lb/> orthodox congregation<lb/> are the people so
                indif<lb/>=ferent or changeable in their<lb/> opinions or has <persName>D<hi
                        rend="sup">r</hi> W.</persName> be<lb/> come more orthodox<lb/> in his
                outward expressi<lb/>=ons &amp; conduct. At least<lb/> his <sic>prevale</sic>
                opinions are<lb/> I am sure not undergone<lb/> a change for <persName>Rev<hi
                        rend="sup">d</hi> Mr Meyer</persName><lb/> rec<hi rend="sup">d</hi> a letter
                from him, ad<lb/>=vising of his call &amp; so treats<lb/> it as a triumph of
                Reform<lb/> &amp; boats<add>?</add> that in less than<lb/> 10 years the whole of
                the<lb/> Jews in the<lb/>
                <placeName>United States</placeName> will be come<lb/> reformers, so that I am</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>of opinion that the Dr<lb/> is an hypocrite, his writings<lb/> lately certainly has a
                differ<lb/>-ent colouring to what his<lb/> precious opinions were<lb/> &amp; his
                essays in your jour<lb/>=nal certainly indicate a very<lb/> great modification at
                least<lb/> of his former negative ideas<lb/> of Messiah &amp; resurrection<lb/>—do
                please enlighten me<lb/> early—in regard to the<lb/> D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>.'s
                call.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please advise me how<lb/> much <persName>Oppenheim</persName> owes
                for<lb/> the Occident as well as <persName>Myers</persName><lb/> are they all
                desirous to pay<lb/>
                <persName>Michl Lazarus</persName> has not paid<lb/> me for a long while, does he
                still<lb/> take the O.? Are there any other<lb/> dues to you <sic>here,</sic>?</p>
            <p>Are we to have any of <persName>Peixotto</persName><lb/>
                <add>?</add>? Hoping you<lb/> are well, in which all your<lb/> friends here unite. I
                remain<lb/> your friend</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Samuel Hart Senr.</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Nov 16 1853</date>
            </p>
